race.comment: BAGGAGE HANDLER (4) has switched yards freshened 54 days, and led and went close two back at Wagga (NSW), but couldn't back it up there after (vet cleared). He will jump and run from the inside barrier and Wiggins' engagement is a decent push for his chances. Well-placed here. DEVINE FORCE (6) has switched from the top Brisbane yard on a 52-day freshen. Maps well and went close at the Gold Coast two back this grade. Cormack is booked and is currently striking at a whopping 34%. BELLA BIANCA (10) led and won an Open comfortably at Atherton and that stacks up. The 2kg claim needs managing but the gate is awkward today. GAMADALE NIP (7) has a similar profile and should be around the mark. SINGULAR (2) has been racing short of his best but would have claims if presented on song back to a short course sprint.
